side_key.statement:
Define φ(C,U,V) = (high(U), c0(U), c0(V)) where high=Phi_{e−1} monic high coeffs of the side (length e−1 = w for free-1) and c0 is the constant term. Then:
  (i)  high+c0 determines the monic side locator, hence U (resp. V) as its root set when fully split with distinct roots;
  (ii) φ(C,U,V)=φ(C',U',V') with fully split sides ⇒ (U,V)=(U',V');
  (iii) the fiber of φ over a side key is a set of pads C (multi-pad);
  (iv) M_pad(z) := max fiber size of φ on ordered top-seam pairs in fiber z satisfies N_ord(z) ≤ M_pad(z) · N_side(z), with equality structure N_ord = sum_keys m_key where m_key = #pads for that side key;
  (v) if M_pad(z)=1 then φ is injective on ordered pairs in the fiber and N_ord(z)=N_side(z).
